cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC 

This paper is primarily focused on the training of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and proposes a new training procedure called Decoupled Greedy Learning (DGL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves large-scale image classification, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical and empirical analysis of the proposed approach, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses parallelization and asynchronous settings, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
